                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Clifford Papers contain several pages of penciled notes in the handwriting of
                    Mr. Clifford, dated May 4, 1948. Some of these notes deal with the question of
                    American recognition of the anticipated Jewish state and read as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <list>
                            <item>“1. Recognition is consistent with U.S. policy from the
                                beginning.</item>
                            <item>“2. A separate Jewish state is inevitable. It will be set up
                                shortly.</item>
                            <item>“3. As far as Russia is concerned we would do better to indicate
                                recognition.</item>
                            <item>“4. We must recognize inevitably. Why not now.</item>
                            <item>“5. State Dept. resolution doesn’t stop partition.”</item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>For other penciled notes of Mr. Clifford, dated May 4, 1948, see the editorial
                    note on <ref target="#pg_744">page 744</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
